                <h2 id=3D"difference" class=3D"text--dark-blue flush-top">W=
hat's the difference between CPC, CPM, and CPA?</h2>
                <p>Similar to CPM, CPC and CPA also exist and serve as othe=
r ways of pricing ads.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>CPC</strong>
                        <p><a href=3D"https://www.webfx.com/ppc/glossary/wh=
at-is-cpc/">CPC, or cost per click</a>, is very similar to CPM. However, wi=
th CPC, you pay for every time someone takes action and clicks on one of yo=
ur ads. This is extremely useful when you're promoting an ultra-specific pr=
oduct or service in a niche market. </p>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>CPA</strong>
                        <p>CPA, or cost per acquisition, is when the promot=
er of the ad only has to pay when a purchase is made that can be tracked ba=
ck to the buyer clicking on the ad that resulted in that purchase.</p>
                        <p>If you're going to utilize CPC or CPA, it's impo=
rtant to have a high click-through rate since the goal of the ads is to ult=
imately have someone purchase the product that you're advertising.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>CPM</strong>
                        <p>With CPM on the other hand, you only pay per 100=
0 impressions. Impressions essentially refer to how many people see your ad=
. They don't have to take action (like clicking the ad) to be considered an=
 impression.</p>
                        <p>Click-through rate is less important with CPM si=
nce you're not as worried about driving conversions as you are increasing b=
rand awareness. This makes CPM rates extremely low and cost-effective.</p>
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h2 id=3D"shouldi" class=3D"text--dark-blue flush-top">Shou=
ld I use CPM, CPA, or CPC?</h2>
                <p>As with every aspect of marketing, different techniques =
will be successful depending on the campaign type.</p>
                <p>CPM often makes the most sense if your company is driven=
 toward increasing awareness for your brand. It is also extremely helpful w=
hen your campaign is aiming to convey a detail-oriented message to your cus=
tomers. It's less focused on clicks and can be low in cost, making it great=
 for low budgets.</p>
                <p>On the other hand, CPC and CPA stand out as a fantastic =
choice if you are using <a href=3D"https://www.webfx.com/digital-advertisin=
g/glossary/what-is-digital-advertising/">digital advertising</a>. If you're=
 focused on doing more than just making an impression on users and your end=
 goal is a purchase, one of these options is the way to go.</p>

                <h2 id=3D"when" class=3D"text--dark-blue flush-top">When sh=
ould you use CPC instead of CPM?</h2>
                <p>If the CPM of your ad campaign is too high to be worth t=
he investment, or if you just aren=E2=80=99t seeing results, a CPC <a href=
=3D"https://www.webfx.com/ppc/services/">PPC</a> campaign might be a better=
 option.</p>
                <p>With <a href=3D"https://www.webfx.com/ppc/glossary/what-=
is-ppc/">pay-per-click advertising, or PPC</a>, you only pay for ads when p=
eople actually click on them. That way, if someone sees your ad and isn=E2=
=80=99t interested, you haven=E2=80=99t lost anything. If you use search en=
gines, you=E2=80=99ve most likely seen PPC ads before.</p>
                <p>In Google, for example, they can appear both at the top =
of the results and in a sidebar next to the results:</p>
                <center><img data-od-added-loading=3D"" data-od-xpath=3D"/H=
TML/BODY/ARTICLE[@id=3D'page-main-content']/*[2][self::DIV]/*[1][self::DIV]=
/*[1][self::DIV]/*[7][self::UL]/*[42][self::CENTER]/*[1][self::IMG]" loadin=
g=3D"lazy" class=3D"responsive-image" src=3D"https://www.webfx.com/wp-conte=
nt/themes/fx/assets/img/tools/cpm-calculator/ppc-example.jpg" width=3D"750p=
x" alt=3D"PPC example">
                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
                </center>
                <p>In this screenshot, every single result shown is actuall=
y a PPC ad. This means that if you were to click on any of them, the site o=
wner would have to pay Google.</p>
                <p>So how does Google (along with other search engines) dec=
ide who to show these ads to?</p>
                <p>When advertisers create PPC campaigns, they choose a set=
 of keywords they want to be listed for. In the example above, all of the a=
ds shown are for businesses that wanted to reach people who searched for =
=E2=80=9Cweb design.=E2=80=9D</p>
                <p>All PPC ads are not priced the same, though. The cost fo=
r each click is determined by an auction process, and each advertiser has t=
o <a href=3D"https://www.webfx.com/ppc/learn/how-does-ppc-bidding-work/">se=
t a bid for the maximum amount</a> they are willing to pay per click for sp=
ecific keywords.</p>
                <p>This means that broad keywords like =E2=80=9Cweb design,=
=E2=80=9D which a lot of companies will want to compete for, are more expen=
sive than specific ones like =E2=80=9Cweb design companies in central Penns=
ylvania.=E2=80=9D The fewer bidders a keyword has, the less you will pay to=
 advertise in its search results.</p>
                <p>For many businesses, PPC allows them to maximize their m=
arketing budget.</p>

                <h2 class=3D"text--dark-blue flush-top">Ready to improve yo=
ur CPM?</h2>
                <p>Although it can take some trial and error to figure out =
which keywords work best for your site, PPC can be a much more cost-effecti=
ve pricing model for your digital advertising efforts than CPM.</p>
                <p>WebFX offers a variety of <a href=3D"https://www.webfx.c=
om/ppc/pricing/">PPC campaign plans</a> to fit any budget. Our customized c=
ampaigns vary in PPC spend, number of keywords, and setup fees, and there i=
s always room for customization.</p>
                <p>If you=E2=80=99re interested in learning more about PPC,=
 or want help setting up a campaign, feel free to <a href=3D"https://www.we=
bfx.com/contact/">contact us</a>! We=E2=80=99re more than happy to help you=
 start maximizing your Internet marketing potential.</p>


        </ul></div>
    </div>
</div></article>

